originalText.text:
I recently had the pleasure of experiencing the acupuncture service at Taiji Body Work, and I must say it was an exceptional and rejuvenating journey.

From the moment I stepped into their serene and welcoming space, I felt a sense of tranquility wash over me. The ambiance itself is calming, with soothing music and a decor that exudes comfort and relaxation.

My acupuncturist was incredibly knowledgeable and professional. They took the time to thoroughly understand my concerns and explained the procedure in detail, putting any apprehensions I had at ease. Their expertise was evident, and I felt confident in their hands throughout the session.

The acupuncture itself was a revelation. Not only was it virtually painless, but I could feel the energy flowing through my body, restoring balance and alleviating the tension I had been carrying. The sensation was both calming and invigorating, and I could sense a noticeable improvement in my overall well-being even after just one session.

What sets Taiji Body Work apart is their holistic approach. They don't just focus on the physical aspect but also consider the mental and emotional aspects of healing. The session left me feeling not just physically relaxed but also mentally rejuvenated.

The cleanliness and attention to detail in their practice were also commendable, ensuring a hygienic and safe environment, which is especially important in any wellness setting.

I highly recommend Taiji Body Work's acupuncture service to anyone seeking not just relief from physical discomfort but a holistic approach to well-being. Their skilled practitioners, serene atmosphere, and commitment to holistic healing make it a top-notch destination for acupuncture and wellness.

I look forward to my next visit and continuing my journey towards better health and harmony at Taiji Body Work.

originalText.text: Made a surprise for my relative, came in advance and paid the full price of the massage, the massage is excellent, but after it was done, they said to pay for the services, the relative gave $10, but they said he should give $20.  when I heard this, I was very indignant because it was a surprise.  and even if my relative were willing to leave a tip, the establishment has absolutely no right to say how much.  and if he didn't have money with him, how was it a gift?!  so I'm very uncomfortable

This the last time I come to this location.
